(1, 'Sade Bamgboye', 'Sade Bamgboye is an associate pastor of Abundant Grace Tabernacle in Barnsley.\n<br/><br/>\nShe has currently taken early retirement from the Civil Service after 27 years in service. She was awarded an MBA from the University of Wales and has also completed a Diploma in Neuro linguistic programming ( NLP) and a foundational course in counselling. \n<br/><br/>\nSade works with her husband as a business development manager for their dental business, Capitol Clinic Limited.\nSade has a passion for building a godly foundation in families and marriages. This is evidenced by her past involvement in the organization of the OFNC biannual married couples’ event, a weekend devoted to helping couples succeed in their marriages. \nAs mentor to many young people, Sade is driven to see them fulfil their God given potential. \n<br/><br/>\nShe is married to Pastor Ebi Bamgboye and they are blessed to have a daughter and a son.\n', 'sade.jpg'),
(2, 'Bidemi Oyedepo', 'Bidemi Oyedepo is lover of Christ and an ardent believer in God’s word. Being passionate about practical Christianity, she leads different groups in the study of the Bible, making it applicable to real life situations. She is a prolific teacher and competent counselor with vast experience working with women and children. \n<br/><br/>\nBidemi Oyedepo is responsible, very flexible and adaptable to change while maintaining her integrity of character. She is known for her unparalleled learning attitude and logical approach to life which enables her to identify and solve problems objectively. She has solid writing and verbal communication skills. Her focus on community development is evident in her contribution to different Christian units and committees where she serves as a leader and key contributor.\n', 'bidemi.jpg'),
(3, 'Oluseye Ashiru', 'Oluseye Ashiru is a John Maxwell Certified Coach, Trainer and Speaker.\nShe is also an Author and also an Online Entrepreneur.\n<br/><br/>\nHer passion is about helping Moms discover, embrace and fulfill their God-given purpose. She believes that it’s possible to be a great mom and to also pursue the full plans and purpose of God for your life. She calls out that seed of greatness inside every mother because she knows that each one has a unique purpose that needs to be expressed and fulfilled.\n<br/><br/>\nShe is the Founder of Moms Achieving Purpose (www.momsachievingpurpose.com), a Community where she mentors other moms and the Lead Coach & Trainer at The Moms Achieving Purpose Academy (www.momsachievingpurposeacademy.com) where she trains and equips mothers with the strategy and structure they need to express their unique purpose.\nShe also blogs at www.momsachievingpurpose.com and she also writes guest posts for Huffington Post and She Leads Africa. \nHer personal space at www.oluseyeashiru.com will give more information about her.\nOluseye is an ordained minister of the gospel with the RCCG and she is happily married with children.\n<br/><br/>\nSOCIAL MEDIA HANDLES:<br/>\nFacebook: Oluseye Ashiru<br/> \nTwitter: @OluseyeAshiru and @PurposeMoms<br/>\nInstagram: @oluseyeashiru and @momsachievingpurpose<br/>\n', 'oluseye.jpg'),
(4, 'Ade Owolabi', 'Ade Owolabi is a down-to-earth, dynamic and passionate communicator of value. He’s a speaker, writer and counselor with an unusual depth in the word. He has keen interest in areas involving PURPOSE and relationship matters particularly the Marriage institution. He has an undying burden to reach, teach and educate couples on “Marriage God’s Way”, as well as truths that make for a complete life.\r\nHe has published two books: “Sex Lies – Sex Truths” for singles and “Sex from Scriptures” for couples and intending couples.<br/><br/>\r\nHe is married to Akpezi and they are blessed with two children, Olamide and Ovie.\r\n<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\nFB: Ade Owolabi<br/>\r\nT: @adekinki<br/>\r\nIG: @ade.owolabi @marriagesettings<br/>\r\nBlog: <a href=\'http://www.discoveryessence.wordpress.com\' target=\'_blank\'>www.discoveryessence.wordpress.com</a>', 'ade.png'),
(5, 'Stacy Kupa', 'Stacy Kupa is the Head of Content for the “A Beautiful Life By Kenny” Initiative. Her desire to see women quickly find their path in life, especially in the area of career is evident in her work.  An education enthusiast whose love for children has led to a shift from her training as a Computer Engineer and spurred her drive towards a career in school administration and development. \r\n', 'stacy_real.png'),
(6, 'Chibuzor Iwobi', 'Chibuzor Iwobi is an economist who has an undying passion for writing. He has published five novels online - Bloodlust Trilogy, Ejime: Two Sides Of a Coin &amp; Ejime: A Broken Coin. Chibuzor hopes to publish several more and one day dreams his novels will be adapted for Tv.&nbsp;\n<div><br></div><div>This more</div>', 'iwobi.jpg'),
(7, 'Ayo Wright', 'Ayo Wright is an Industrial Chemistry graduate from Caleb University (and a graduate from University of Bedfordshire with a Masters of Environmental Management).<br/><br/>He is a storyteller, blogger, and poet.  He loves using words to positively impact and inspire generations via his interests – writing, poetry, and environmental sustainability. <br/>Find him on Twitter <a href=\'http://twitter.com/atothewizz\' target=\'_blank\'>@atothewizz<a>\n', 'ayo.jpg');

