nt-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\"><img src=\"http://localhost:8080/blogs/1505483321about Mrs X.jpg\" alt=\"\"><br></span><p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: start; \"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\nHelvetica;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: start; \"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\nHelvetica;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">Hello ladies!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:Helvetica;mso-bidi-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">I will be using this platform to document my journey to\nfinding me.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:Helvetica;mso-bidi-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">Before I start writing and plaguing you with weekly\narticles, I\'ve been told I have to talk about me a bit.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:Helvetica;mso-bidi-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">Why exactly do I even have to talk about me sef? Do I really\nhave to? Aaarrggghhh....<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:Helvetica;mso-bidi-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">Do you know the feeling you get when you simply don\'t want\nto look into the mirror because you believe you won\'t like what you see? (I\nknow some of you have never felt this way, and I am envious of, and so happy\nfor, you, and serving you major side eye!) Anyway, for those of you who can\nrelate to what I\'m saying, this is how I\'ve felt for the past six years.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:Helvetica;mso-bidi-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">To help lift the veil off the mirror very slowly, I will\nstart with who I was before my \"mirror phobia\", who I feel I am at the moment,\nand who I would love to be.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:Helvetica;mso-bidi-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">I used to be a keen God lover and an earnest God chaser. You\nknow those Christian sisters in Uni who could pray for hours, quietly listening\nfor God\'s voice while staring up at the stars? Yep, I was one of those! I was deeply\nin love with my heavenly Father. Apart from being a God lover, I was a business\nowner, head of a student organization, worshipper, part of my church\'s youth\nleadership, brilliant student, and I think I was quite beautiful too! I had\ndreams of becoming a business owner, philanthropist, devoted mom, and a wife\nwhom her husband respected and completely adored.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:Helvetica;mso-bidi-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">Now, let me tell you who I feel I am at the moment. Without\nlifting the veil off the mirror more than an inch, I feel I have let my heavenly\nFather down in every way possible. I see myself as a fat, mostly unhappy,\nstay-at-home mom, who has lived in three countries and five states in the past\nseven years. (Trust me, I have now become an expert at not being too\ncomfortable in one location because I will end up packing up again, and moving\nanyway.)<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:Helvetica;mso-bidi-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">As for whom I would like to be, let\'s just say I want to be\nthat girl that makes her heavenly Father very proud.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:Helvetica;mso-bidi-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">So, people, till I find me, just call me Mrs X!</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Raleway;\">&nbsp;</span></p><!--EndFragment--></p>', '', '2017-10-30 05:53:29', '', 51),
(7, 'Victory', '<p><img src=\"http://localhost:8080/blogs/1509343479WhatsApp Image 2017-10-25 at 12.53.19 PM.jpeg\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">As I climbed on the treadmill reluctantly putting one foot in front of the other, I felt tired and just not in the mood. By the 22nd minute, I couldn\'t take it any longer and I made to stop but an inner voice said KEEP GOING so I did, gradually picking up speed again till I finished the 30 minutes work out.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Do you feel like stopping? Like giving up? That your change will never come? That the situation is hopeless? The Lord, the gracious One, Omnipotent, loving and merciful God says KEEP GOING.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">He says - With Him nothing shall be impossible, KEEP GOING.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">He says - you and I will fulfill purpose, KEEP GOING.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">He says victory is assured and only His will concerning us shall stand, KEEP GOING.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">KEEP GOING my friends! You might be feeling overwhelmed as I felt and wanted to stop when I was almost at the finish line. Don\'t stop. KEEP GOING. Feelings are fickle and it\'s darkest just before the break of dawn KEEP GOING...</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Isaiah 40:31 says we shall mount up with wings like eagles, we shall run and not be weary.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Apply this to every area of your life.. your business, your marriage, your studies, your work, that difficult project, that new initiative, KEEP GOING.</span></p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br></span><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">KEEP GOING, VICTORY IS UPON YOU.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Song: He has given us victory&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">We will lift Him higher</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Jehovah, we will lift Him higher.............</span></p>', '', '2017-10-30 06:04:47', '', 1),
(8, 'Nothing can stop God\'s plan', '<p><img src=\"http://localhost:8080/blogs/1509343621WhatsApp Image 2017-10-25 at 12.55.31 PM.jpeg\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">I love this simple and straightforward scripture in Isaiah7:7 and use it a lot:</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Thus says the Lord GOD: It will not take place, it will not happen!</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">My dear friend, what are your SECRET FEARS? The Lord God sent me to tell you that&nbsp; It will not stand, nor shall it come to pass ( NKJV). Rather I want you to declare this week and beyond the word of God in Jeremiah 29:11 that says; \"His thoughts towards us are GOOD and NOT EVIL to give us a FUTURE and a HOPE and to bring us to AN&nbsp; EXPECTED END\".</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Be expectant!</span></p>', '', '2017-10-30 06:07:04', '', 1);
INSERT INTO `blogs` (`id`, `title`, `body`, `author`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `views`) VALUES
(9, 'Whatever you bind', '<p><img src=\"http://localhost:8080/blogs/1509343858WhatsApp Image 2017-10-25 at 12.56.31 PM.jpeg\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br></span></p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br></span><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Assuredly I say to YOU, whatever YOU bind on earth will be bound in heaven, and whatever YOU loose on earth will be loosed in heaven (Matthew 18:18,16:19). Some of us use this scripture only for binding demons while indeed Binding refers to ALL things that YOU do NOT permit as a child of God while Loosing refers to things that YOU permit. Whatever YOU do not permit (forbid) this week and beyond e.g. lack, loneliness, disunity, marital problems etc, will be forbidden in heaven as well IJMN and whatever YOU permit (declare, allow) here on earth e.g. promotion, favour, good health, God\'s protection, provision, soundness of mind etc&nbsp; heaven will back YOU up IJMN.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">As we celebrate Nigeria\'s 57th birthday we in one accord forbid all the evil plaguing this nation- we forbid kidnapping, killings, terrorism, armed robbery attacks, all forms of agitation and unrest is forbidden IJMN. We forbid greed, materialism, the love of money which is the root of evil IJMN. Rather we permit PEACE, CONTENTMENT, GODLINESS, LOVE, WISE DECISIONS AND TRUE FAITH WHICH FOCUSES ON ETERNITY IJMN, AMEN. Please let\'s remember Christ in all we do this week and be led by His Spirit. Remember, each and every child of God has been given the keys to the Kingdom, USE It. It shall be well with us IJMN.</span></p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br></span><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">&nbsp;Be Motivated!</span></p>', '', '2017-10-30 06:11:19', '', 1),
(10, 'Do unto others as you would have them do unto you', '<p><img src=\"http://localhost:8080/blogs/1509343902WhatsApp Image 2017-10-25 at 12.57.23 PM.jpeg\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Matthew 7:12 says \"Whatever you want men to do to you, do also to them.\"&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">This is a very powerful scripture as it turns our attention off ourselves and our own needs and shifts the focus unto others. This scripture is commonly known as the GOLDEN RULE as it focuses on doing something good for others.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">This rule is the foundation of ACTIVE GOODNESS, MERCY and LOVE - the kind of love God shows to us everyday.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Oya, my people think of a good deed you can do for someone today, all through this week and beyond. This week encourage someone, compliment them, pray for someone, share someone\'s burden, listen to them, give someone a gift etc. Anything good that you would like done to you, do for someone else today and for the rest of the week and see how God will do much more in your life.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">God bless us all!</span></p>', '', '2017-10-30 06:11:55', '', 1),
(11, 'Under the rock', '<p><img src=\"http://localhost:8080/blogs/1509343947WhatsApp Image 2017-10-25 at 12.58.37 PM.jpeg\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">We are under the Rock, the Rock that\'s higher than us, Jehovah hides us, we are under the Rock, Go tell our enemies we are under the Rock, Jehovah hides us, we are under the Rock.( SONG)</span></p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br></span><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Christ is our ROCK and as our Rock we can be sure of His Protection ( Rocks do just that, PROTECT..go and ask the people of EgbalandðŸ˜€). You can be sure of His Provision, (He met the Israelites physical need for water by giving them water to quench their thirst while also giving them Life as they were DYING of thirst). He performed a miracle for them, so shall He do for us and much more IJN. We can draw strength from our Rock ( who or what else is stronger than a rock)? He is the Dependable One, He can never let you down. Under the Rock no evil can touch us for the Bible says in Colossians 3:3 that our lives are hidden with Christ in God. At the end of this week we will only have cause to magnify and glorify His Holy Name IJMN. Stay connected to the Rock of Ages.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">Stay Motivated!</span></p>', '', '2017-10-30 06:12:35', '', 1),
(12, 'People & Tigers', '<p><img src=\"http://localhost:8080/blogs/1509343981WhatsApp Image 2017-10-25 at 1.17.13 PM.jpeg\"><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">People are like grass;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">their beauty is like a flower in the field.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">The grass withers and the flower fades.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">But the word of the Lord remains forever.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">In 1 Peter 24-25, people are compared to grass and flowers which though beautiful, will eventually fade away.We are reminded that everything in this life - possessions, accomplishments, even people will fade away and disappear but guess what?</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">ONLY GOD\'S WILL,WORD &amp; WORK are permanent. Let\'s stop grasping the temporary and begin focusing our time, money and energy on the permanent.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\">No</span></p>', '', '2017-11-02 14:47:19', '', 1);

