-style-name:\"Table Normal\";\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\n	mso-style-priority:99;\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\n	mso-padding-alt:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt;\n	mso-para-margin-top:0cm;\n	mso-para-margin-right:0cm;\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:10.0pt;\n	mso-para-margin-left:0cm;\n	line-height:115%;\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\n	font-size:11.0pt;\n	font-family:Calibri;\n	mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;\n	mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;\n	mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri;\n	mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;}\n</style>\n<![endif]-->\n\n\n\n<!--StartFragment-->\n\n<p style=\"line-height: 115%; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial;\ncolor:#222222\">God is highly strategic in His reasoning. He is the master\nstrategist!<br>\nAfter God made man, He gave him a crucial instruction in Genesis 2:16-17 \"<em>And the Lord God commanded man, saying, of\nevery tree of the garden thou mayest freely eat, but of the tree of the\nknowledge of good and evil, thou shalt not eat of it, for in the day that thou\neatest thereof thou shalt surely die.\"<br>\n</em>Do you recall that as important as that particular instruction was, God did\nnot repeat it to the woman when she was brought into the scene?<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"line-height: 115%; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial;\ncolor:#222222\">When God was going to destroy the world with flood, He spoke to\nNoah about a crucial \'rescue plan\' which He again, didn\'t tell Mrs. Noah\ndirectly; do you recall? (Genesis 6:13-22). When God was going to give Abraham\na crucial instruction/test that\'ll form the basis for the blessings we enjoy\ntoday, He told him without involving Sarah. He did the same thing when He was\ngoing to make a covenant with him (Abraham); in fact, Grandpa Abraham was to\n\'sacrifice\' their only son and God left him with the \'task\' of carrying out\nthis \'impossible assignment\' that would include \'managing\' Grandma Sarah in the\nprocess; do you recall? (Genesis 17; 18...). I could go on and on but I\'ll stop\nhere for simplicity sake. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"line-height: 115%; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial;\ncolor:#222222\">The idea was not to shut the Woman out of the plan, neither was\nit a way of segregation or discrimination. Man is the one God named as HEAD and\nas such, he must be able to perform the key, basic and highly significant role\nof DISSEMINATION/COMMUNICATION. According to God\'s design, man must be able to\neffectively communicate \'the word\', \'the vision\', \'the promise\', \'the\ntask/project\', \'the direction\', as received or perceived from God to his wife/family\nas occasion demands. Man must be an effective COMMUNICATOR and not a fiery \'<em>Terminator</em>\' to his household. Moses\nperformed this role between God and the Israelites; Jesus did and still does\nthe same today between God and his bride - the Church.<br>\nIn the same vein, the Woman must submit to benefit from her \"<em>God-ordained teacher</em>\" and head in the\nperson of her beloved husband. If submission is not in place, the ability of\nthe man to perform this crucial role is highly undermined and the ultimate will\nof God for that union may be thwarted (God forbid!)<br>\nIt is impossible to benefit from or enjoy the unction you do not respect or\nregard. There is an unction and grace in every man to function by design\nparticularly when he is in Christ.<br>\nMatthew 10:41 KJV <em>\"He that receiveth\na prophet in the name of a prophet shall receive a prophet\'s reward; and he\nthat receiveth a righteous man in the name of a righteous man shall receive a </em>righteous<em> man\'s reward.\"</em> Respect establishes\na flow of virtue from one medium to the other, from a scientific point of view,\nthe place of \'potential difference\' cannot be overemphasized.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"line-height: 115%; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial;\ncolor:#222222\">I am not in any way saying that the woman cannot access God\ndirectly, but <em>God is a God of order</em>.\nHe will not boycott the order He Himself established in that <em>Christ is the head of the man, while the man\nis the head of his wife</em> (1 Corinthians 11:4). There are things that God\nwill rather tell the head, thus leaving the head with the responsibility of\nproperly communicating the same to his wife; God respects order.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"line-height: 115%; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial;\ncolor:#222222\">Men, we must understand that we need to relate with our wives in\nways that engenders honour and respect. We must be responsible and sensitive to\nher unvoiced feelings, this might be tough but we get to learn the ropes with\nthe right attitude in place. It is difficult to respect an unrepentantly\nirresponsible man!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"line-height: 115%; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial;\ncolor:#222222\">Dear husband, be a man and not a <em>\'Man O War\'</em> in the home. Be approachable, loving, considerate, and\nfirm when necessary. Be a balanced leader and not a boss. Be a teacher and not\na Lecturer, be a leader and not a master; be a lover and not an abuser; be a <strong>communicator</strong> and not an authoritarian.\nYes, you are the head but then don\'t lose your head! If God has trusted you\nwith that crucial role/position and entrusted a whole woman into your hands\nthen, you must be accountable to Him who has trusted you that much!<br>\nDear wife, allow your husband take the lead. Listen to him, support him, and\npray ceaselessly for him. It doesn\'t mean he will always be right but he will\nbe used to being a man. Your opinion is also important even if he doesn\'t see\nthat immediately; with time, he will learn to value your thoughts more.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"line-height: 115%; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-family:Arial;\ncolor:#222222\">I am a man, but not a chauvinist!<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<!--EndFragment-->', 'her_unique_man.jpg', '2018-02-03 16:17:49', 'Her \'Unique\' man', 100, 0);
