e=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\n  line-height:150%;font-family:Garamond\">Big sphere of influence<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n  </td>\r\n  <td width=\"189\" valign=\"top\" style=\"width:189.05pt;border-top:none;border-left:\r\n  none;border-bottom:solid black 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-themecolor:text1;\r\n  border-right:solid black 1.0pt;mso-border-right-themecolor:text1;mso-border-top-alt:\r\n  solid black .5pt;mso-border-top-themecolor:text1;mso-border-left-alt:solid black .5pt;\r\n  mso-border-left-themecolor:text1;mso-border-alt:solid black .5pt;mso-border-themecolor:\r\n  text1;padding:0cm 5.4pt 0cm 5.4pt\">\r\n  <p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"margin-left: 0cm; margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: 150%;\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\n  line-height:150%;font-family:Garamond\">Small sphere of influence<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n  </td>\r\n </tr>\r\n</tbody></table>\r\n\r\n<span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;\r\nfont-family:Garamond\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:150%\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:\r\n12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:Garamond\">Compare the two women; they both\r\nused the tools they had. Deborah used her <strong><em>education</em>,</strong> while Jael used her <strong><em>nail\r\nand hammer</em></strong>, but there were many similarities between them.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:150%;mso-outline-level:1\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\nline-height:150%;font-family:Garamond\">How can we become Nation builders? <o:p></o:p></span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:150%;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo3\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\r\nGaramond;mso-fareast-font-family:Garamond;mso-bidi-font-family:Garamond\">(a)<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp; </span></span></strong><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\nline-height:150%;font-family:Garamond\">Be aware:</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:Garamond\"> &nbsp;Read newspapers, be up to date on news and\r\nhappenings. Get on social media, choose a platform and use that tool wisely.\r\nPick up a burden for this nation.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:\r\n150%;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\r\nGaramond;mso-fareast-font-family:Garamond;mso-bidi-font-family:Garamond\">(b)<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp; </span></span></strong><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\nline-height:150%;font-family:Garamond\">What is in your hand? (as God asked\r\nMoses):</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;\r\nfont-family:Garamond\"> Is it education, native sense, wisdom, &nbsp;career, encouraging your husband to do the\r\nright things (if he is highly placed in church or in the secular world)? Don\'t\r\nencourage your husband to compromise. One question I always ask myself when I\r\nsee people, in exalted positions, mess up is, \"Don\'t these people have wives\r\nwho can tell them the truth, or are the wives also enjoying the ill-gotten\r\nwealth?\" <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:\r\n150%;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\r\nGaramond;mso-fareast-font-family:Garamond;mso-bidi-font-family:Garamond\">(c)<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp; </span></span></strong><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\nline-height:150%;font-family:Garamond\">Spread best practice: </span></strong><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:Garamond\">Be\r\nexcellent at what you do and spread best practice. Very few people excel in politics,\r\nbeyond the place of being called a minister or governor; how much difference\r\ncan we make if the system is very corrupt? If we can\'t make much, then let\'s\r\nfocus on our area of influence and spread best practice. One very good way to\r\ndo this is that you continue to train and retrain yourself. Education is a\r\nlifelong endeavour.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:\r\n150%;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\r\nGaramond;mso-fareast-font-family:Garamond;mso-bidi-font-family:Garamond\">(d)<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp; </span></span></strong><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\nline-height:150%;font-family:Garamond\">Mentor people:</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:Garamond\">\r\nFocus on the younger ones and indeed anyone that is in your field who you feel\r\nneeds help. Not everything is competition. As you help others, God will enlarge\r\nyou. When you open your hand wide, you get more. Leave a legacy.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:\r\n150%;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\r\nGaramond;mso-fareast-font-family:Garamond;mso-bidi-font-family:Garamond\">(e)<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp; </span></span></strong><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\nline-height:150%;font-family:Garamond\">Redefine your vision, motive or\r\nphilosophy:</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:\r\n150%;font-family:Garamond\"> Visions evolve. The more understanding you have,\r\nthe clearer things become. Your vision can, in fact, be amended to reflect your\r\ndeeper understanding, and let it have something that will benefit others as\r\ndisadvantaged or marginalized people. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:\r\n150%;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo3\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\r\nGaramond;mso-fareast-font-family:Garamond;mso-bidi-font-family:Garamond\">(f)<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;\r\n</span></span></strong><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:Garamond\">Enlarge\r\nyour territory (1 Chronicles 4:10):</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:Garamond\"> Expansion is\r\ngood, but must be handled with care, and must be God-led. However, it is a good\r\nway to <strong>be the change</strong>. You are\r\nenlarging your sphere of influence and spreading best practice when you employ\r\nmore people (job creation). The main problem in Nigeria is not Boko Haram, as\r\nmy husband would say, it is unemployment. Recently, the Nigerian President\r\nspoke of efforts being made to create job opportunities for people. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:150%;\r\nmso-list:l0 level1 lfo3\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:\r\nGaramond;mso-fareast-font-family:Garamond;mso-bidi-font-family:Garamond\">(g)<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp; </span></span></strong><!--[endif]--><strong><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;\r\nline-height:150%;font-family:Garamond\">Pray for your leaders</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:Garamond\"> <strong>(1Tim 2:1-2):</strong> The Bible urges us to\r\npray for our leaders, so that we may live peaceful lives.<strong> </strong>Our National Anthem compels us \"... to serve with heart and might,\r\nwith love, strength and faith....\" Remember that we are all leaders, not just\r\nthose in the recognized seat of power. We lead others around us at our offices,\r\nin our homes (our children), our churches, so every one of us also has to serve\r\nwith our heart, might, love, strength, and faith. Let us all pray for one\r\nanother.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height:150%\"><span lang=\"EN-GB\" style=\"font-size:\r\n12.0pt;line-height:150%;font-family:Garamond\">Women, let us start with our\r\nhomes, and gradually move to the church and nation. <strong>Be the Change!<o:p></o:p></strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n<!--EndFragment-->', '0');
